headline: Kroger-Albertsons Merger Blocked by Court, Handing Victory to Biden Antitrust Enforcers
summary: The ruling hands a victory to Biden antitrust enforcers, who said the $20 billion supermarket merger would erode competition and raise prices for consumers.

headline: Kroger Jumps As Judge Blocks Biggest Grocery Merger In History
summary: A district judge ruled Kroger's $24.6 billion takeover of Albertsons would reduce competition for U.S. grocery shoppers, likely squelching the deal.

headline: The Year’s Best Dow Stock Not Named Nvidia
summary: Walmart  customers consider the retailer a happy place because of its low prices and “rollback” sales.  Nvidia  is the only stock in the  this year that has done better than Walmart, soaring nearly 175%.  The nearly unanimous answer from analysts is yes; 37 of the 41 sell-siders who follow the stock have Walmart rated a “Buy” or “Outperform,” compared with just three “Holds” and one “Sell.”

headline: Instacart price target raised to $56 from $49 at Loop Capital
summary: Loop Capital raised the firm’s price target on Instacart (CART) to $56 from $49 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The firm contends that the company is positioned to maintain leadership in helping grocers migrate their businesses to better serve digital consumers, also noting that Walmart’s (WMT) success in the sector is encouraging and likely signals an accelerated pace of development for other grocers, the analyst tells investors in a research note. headline: Is Artificial Intelligence Stock Symbotic a Buy?
summary: The debut of OpenAI's ChatGPT in late 2022 helped to kick off an artificial intelligence (AI) frenzy.  One company investors might want to consider is robotics specialist Symbotic (NASDAQ: SYM).  The global warehouse automation market was worth over $23 billion in 2023, and it is forecast to reach $41 billion by 2027.
